# PreciosYa — Project Context & TODO for Codex

> **Read this entire file before touching any code.**
> This is the single source of truth for the project. Every architectural decision, every naming convention, every technology choice is documented here.

---

## 1. What is PreciosYa?

PreciosYa is a SaaS web application for Argentine small business owners (kiosk owners, corner stores, bakeries, resellers) that helps them:

1. Calculate sale prices automatically from cost + desired margin
2. Apply Argentina's official monthly inflation index (IPC from INDEC) to all product costs in one tap
3. Get real-time alerts when a product's margin drops below a configured minimum
4. Generate a shareable PNG price list for WhatsApp or printing
5. Track the price history of every product over time

**The core insight:** 94% of Argentine small merchants update prices manually (paper, memory, Excel). There is no simple mobile-first tool that integrates the official INDEC inflation API. PreciosYa fills that gap.

---

## 2. Tech Stack

### Monorepo structure (pnpm workspaces)
```
preciosya/
├── apps/
│   ├── web/          → React 18 + Vite + TypeScript + Tailwind CSS + PWA
│   └── api/          → Node.js 20 + Express 4 + TypeScript
├── packages/
│   └── shared/       → Shared TypeScript types + PricingEngine
├── .cursorrules
├── package.json
└── pnpm-workspace.yaml
```

### Frontend (`apps/web`)
- **Framework:** React 19 with TypeScript (strict mode)
- **Build:** Vite 8
- **Styles:** Tailwind CSS v4 (`@import "tailwindcss"`, `@utility` en `index.css`) — UI base diseñada con **Kombai**; mantener tokens y componentes existentes
- **PWA:** vite-plugin-pwa + Workbox (offline support via IndexedDB)
- **Routing:** React Router v6
- **State:** TanStack Query (server state) + React Context (auth)
- **Forms:** React Hook Form + Zod
- **Charts:** Chart.js
- **HTTP:** Axios with JWT interceptors
- **Export:** html2canvas (PNG generation, runs in browser)
- **Share:** Web Share API (native WhatsApp sharing)
- **Supabase SDK:** used ONLY for auth (login/logout) and Realtime (notifications)

### Backend (`apps/api`)
- **Runtime:** Node.js 20 + TypeScript (strict mode)
- **Framework:** Express 4
- **ORM:** Prisma 5
- **Database:** Supabase (PostgreSQL 15) — NO RLS, all access control is done in Express middlewares
- **Auth:** Supabase Auth (Google OAuth 2.0) + JWT verification in middleware
- **Storage:** Supabase Storage (bucket: `price-lists`) for PNG/PDF files
- **Scheduler:** node-cron (monthly IPC fetch, daily BCRA rate fetch)
- **Emails:** Resend
- **Validation:** Zod on every incoming request body

### External APIs
- **INDEC IPC (multi-serie):** ver [`docs/IPC_SOURCES.md`](docs/IPC_SOURCES.md) y `apps/api/src/services/ipc-fetch/`
- **BCRA rate:** `https://api.bcra.gob.ar/estadisticas/v3.0/monetarias/reservas`
- **Google OAuth:** managed entirely by Supabase Auth

### No RLS
Supabase Row Level Security is **disabled**. All data access control happens in the Express backend via `authMiddleware` and `ownerGuard`. The frontend uses the Supabase `anon` key only for auth and Realtime. All business data goes through the REST API.

### Deployed stack (troubleshooting default)

- **Web (app):** Vercel proyecto `web` — producción **`https://preciosya.vercel.app`** (alias principal); preview `web-rho-ten-99.vercel.app`.
- **Landing:** Vercel `preciosya-landing` — **`https://preciosya-landing.vercel.app`** → enlaces a la app en `preciosya.vercel.app`.
- **API:** Railway — `https://api-production-3626.up.railway.app`; `FRONTEND_URL` debe incluir `https://preciosya.vercel.app`.

### Policy for AI assistants (read before suggesting URLs)

- **No asumir localhost** cuando el usuario reporta fallos en producción, CORS, login, o “no carga”: el modelo operativo por defecto es **Vercel (web) + Railway (API)**.
- **No** indicar como paso principal “abrí `http://localhost:3001`” ni “probá en `http://localhost:5173`” salvo que el usuario diga explícitamente que desarrolla en local o pida `pnpm dev`.
- **Railway MCP:** remoto en `https://mcp.railway.com` (config en `.cursor/mcp.json`). Usarlo para **logs de deploy, runtime, y errores del servicio** en lugar de inferir desde máquina local. Documentación: [Railway Remote MCP](https://docs.railway.com/ai/remote-mcp-server).
- **Vercel MCP:** ya configurado para proyectos front cuando haga falta.

**Localhost** aplica solo a desarrollo local (`pnpm dev`); los valores de ejemplo están en `apps/*/.env.example`, no son el default mental para soporte en producción.

