## 6. API Endpoints

All routes prefixed with `/api`. All routes except `POST /api/auth/google` require a valid JWT in `Authorization: Bearer <token>`.

### Auth
```
POST /api/auth/google         → login/register with Supabase token
POST /api/auth/refresh        → refresh token
POST /api/auth/logout         → invalidate session
GET  /api/auth/me             → current user profile
```

### Locals
```
GET  /api/locals              → list user's locals
POST /api/locals              → create local (plan limit checked)
PUT  /api/locals/:id          → update local
```

### Categories
```
GET  /api/categories?localId= → list categories
POST /api/categories          → create category
PUT  /api/categories/:id      → update category
DEL  /api/categories/:id      → delete (products become uncategorized)
```

### Products
```
GET  /api/products?localId=&categoryId=&isAlert=&search=&page=&limit=
POST /api/products            → create (plan limit checked, sale_price calculated)
PUT  /api/products/:id        → update (recalculate sale_price, update is_margin_alert)
DEL  /api/products/:id        → soft delete (is_active = false)
GET  /api/products/:id/history → price history (last 50 entries)
PUT  /api/products/bulk-update → { localId, categoryId?, increasePct }
```

### IPC & Economic Indices
```
GET  /api/ipc/latest          → latest IPC and BCRA values from DB
GET  /api/ipc/history         → last 12 months of indices
PUT  /api/locals/:id/apply-ipc → apply latest IPC to all products of a local
```

### Exports
```
POST /api/exports/price-list  → upload PNG (multipart/form-data), save to Supabase Storage, create price_lists record
```

### Notifications
```
GET  /api/notifications?page=      → paginated list
GET  /api/notifications/unread-count → { count }
PUT  /api/notifications/:id/read   → mark one as read
PUT  /api/notifications/read-all   → mark all as read
```

### Admin (requires is_admin flag on user)
```
GET  /api/admin/users?page=&search=
PUT  /api/admin/users/:id/plan
GET  /api/admin/stats
GET  /api/admin/indices
POST /api/admin/ipc/force-fetch    → manually trigger the INDEC scheduler
```

### Health
```
GET  /health → { status: 'ok', timestamp, version }
```

---

## 7. API Response Format

Every response from the API follows this structure:

```typescript
// Success
{ success: true, data: T }

// Error
{ success: false, error: { message: string, code: string } }
```

HTTP status codes used:
- `200` OK
- `201` Created
- `400` Bad Request (validation error)
- `401` Unauthorized (no token or invalid token)
- `403` Forbidden (valid token but insufficient plan or wrong owner)
- `404` Not Found
- `429` Too Many Requests (rate limit)
- `500` Internal Server Error (unexpected)

---

## 8. Frontend Route Structure

```
/                   → redirect to /dashboard if logged in, else /login
/login              → LoginPage (Google OAuth button)
/dashboard          → DashboardPage (summary cards + margin alerts)
/products           → ProductsPage (full product list)
/categories         → CategoriesPage
/price-list         → PriceListPage (generate + share PNG)
/history            → HistoryPage (IPC history + per-product charts)
/settings           → SettingsPage (local config, account, plan)
/admin              → AdminPage (only if user.is_admin)
```

All routes under `/dashboard` and below are wrapped in `ProtectedRoute`.

